ZH: 请你要记得随时保持礼貌。
EN: Please remember to always be polite.

ZH: 她向我问好得非常有礼貌。
EN: She greeted me very politely.

ZH: 礼貌是与人相处的基本原则。
EN: Politeness is a basic principle in interpersonal relationships.

ZH: 他的母亲教导他要对每个人都保持礼貌。
EN: His mother taught him to be polite to everyone.

ZH: 在中国文化中，礼貌非常重要。
EN: Politeness is very important in Chinese culture.

ZH: 他非常懂得如何使用恰当的礼貌用语。
EN: He knows how to use appropriate polite expressions very well.

ZH: 公共场合要维持良好的礼貌。
EN: Good manners should be maintained in public places.

ZH: 礼貌反映了一个人的素质和教养。
EN: Politeness reflects a person's quality and upbringing.

ZH: 在任何语言中，礼貌都是互相尊重的表现。
EN: Politeness is a manifestation of mutual respect in any language.

ZH: 我们应该尽量避免使用粗鲁的言辞，相反要保持礼貌。
EN: We should try to avoid using rude words and instead maintain politeness.

ZH: 你要始终保持礼貌，不管在什么情况下。
EN: You should always maintain politeness, no matter what the situation is.

ZH: 礼貌的行为能够建立积极的社交关系。
EN: Polite behavior can help build positive social relationships.

ZH: 在公交车上要给老人让座是非常礼貌的行为。
EN: Giving up seats to the elderly on buses is a very polite gesture.

ZH: 礼貌是一个人最基本的社交技能之一。
EN: Politeness is one of the most basic social skills a person can have.

ZH: 请你向老师问好时要有礼貌。
EN: Please greet the teacher politely.

ZH: 礼貌在社交交往中起到了缓和关系的作用。
EN: Politeness plays a role in easing interpersonal relationships.

ZH: 在遇到困难时，彼此友好和礼貌的对待是很重要的。
EN: It is important to treat each other with friendliness and politeness when encountering difficulties.

ZH: 礼貌的笑容可以化解尴尬的局面。
EN: A polite smile can defuse an awkward situation.

ZH: 与他人交往要时刻保持礼貌和尊重。
EN: Always maintain politeness and respect when interacting with others.

ZH: 礼貌可以在不同的文化背景下建立友好关系。
EN: Politeness can help establish friendly relationships across different cultural backgrounds.

ZH: 无论何时何地，我们都应该向他人表示礼貌。
EN: We should show politeness to others no matter when or where.
